# API Standards & Shared Contract

## Response Envelope — always this shape

```typescript
// Success
{
  "success": true,
  "data": T,
  "meta": {              // optional — for paginated lists
    "total": 42,
    "page": 1,
    "perPage": 20
  },
  "message": "Created"  // optional — human-readable confirmation
}

// Error
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "DOCUMENT_NOT_FOUND",   // machine-readable, SCREAMING_SNAKE
    "message": "Document not found", // human-readable
    "details": [...]                  // optional — validation field errors
  }
}
```

## Error Codes (add as you build)
| Code | HTTP Status | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Request body/query failed Zod schema |
| `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Resource does not exist |
| `UNAUTHORIZED` | 401 | Missing / invalid auth token |
| `FORBIDDEN` | 403 | Authenticated but not allowed |
| `CONFLICT` | 409 | Duplicate resource |
| `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Unhandled server failure |
| `AI_EXTRACTION_FAILED` | 502 | Upstream AI service error |

## Shared Types Location
All request/response types live in `shared/src/types/` — import from there in both backend and frontend.

```typescript
// ✅ backend controller
import type { Document, ApiResponse } from '@shared/types';

// ✅ frontend service
import type { Document, ApiResponse } from '@shared/types';

// ❌ never define Document in two places
```

## Path Alias
Both workspaces configure `@shared/*` → `../shared/src/*` in their tsconfig.

## URL Conventions
- Base: `/api/v1/<resource>`
- Collections: plural noun — `/documents`
- Single resource: `/documents/:id`
- Actions on resource: `/documents/:id/extract`
- Cross-resource action: `/query` under `/documents`
- HTTP verbs are semantic — `GET` read, `POST` create/action, `PUT` full replace, `PATCH` partial update, `DELETE` remove

## Pagination (when lists grow)
Query params: `?page=1&perPage=20&sort=createdAt&order=desc`

## Date Format
Always ISO-8601 strings: `"2026-07-18T06:17:00.000Z"` — never Unix timestamps in JSON

## File Upload
- Field name: `file` (single) or `files` (multiple)
- `multipart/form-data`
- Metadata fields (category, description) sent as additional form fields, not JSON body
